<p class="eyebrow">Support / Softphone / MicroSIP</p>
<h1>Configure MicroSIP for VoiceTel.</h1>
<p class="lede">MicroSIP is a free, lightweight Windows-only softphone built on PJSIP. Configuration is straightforward — one Account dialog, no nested menus.</p>

<section class="section-block">
	<h2>Steps</h2>
	<ol>
		<li>Open MicroSIP → click the down-arrow next to the account selector → <strong>Add Account</strong>.</li>
		<li>Fill in the Account dialog:
			<ul>
				<li><strong>Account Name:</strong> VoiceTel</li>
				<li><strong>SIP Server:</strong> SIP server host (shown in the customer portal)</li>
				<li><strong>SIP Proxy:</strong> leave blank (uses SIP Server)</li>
				<li><strong>Username:</strong> SIP username from VoiceTel onboarding</li>
				<li><strong>Domain:</strong> same as SIP Server</li>
				<li><strong>Login:</strong> same as Username (auth user)</li>
				<li><strong>Password:</strong> SIP password from onboarding</li>
				<li><strong>Display Name:</strong> caller's name</li>
				<li><strong>Voicemail Number:</strong> blank unless onboarding gave one</li>
				<li><strong>Transport:</strong> UDP</li>
				<li><strong>Public Address:</strong> Auto (or leave blank)</li>
				<li><strong>Register on Startup:</strong> ticked</li>
				<li><strong>Allow Rewrite Contact Header:</strong> ticked</li>
				<li><strong>Allow Via Rewrite:</strong> ticked</li>
				<li><strong>Encryption:</strong> None (or SRTP if onboarding required encrypted media)</li>
			</ul>
		</li>
		<li>Click <strong>Save</strong>. The status bar at the bottom of the main window should change to <strong>Online</strong>.</li>
	</ol>
</section>

<section class="section-block">
	<h2>Codec preferences</h2>
	<p>Open <strong>Tools → Account → Codecs</strong>. Enable PCMU, PCMA, and G.729.</p>
</section>

<section class="section-block">
	<h2>Auto-answer / hotline mode</h2>
	<p>MicroSIP supports auto-answer and hotline modes useful for kiosk-style deployments. Configure under <strong>Account → Advanced → Auto-Answer code</strong> if needed.</p>
</section>

<aside class="cta-block" aria-labelledby="microsip-cta-heading">
	<h2 id="microsip-cta-heading">Need provisioning XML?</h2>
	<p>MicroSIP supports loading account credentials from an XML file at startup — useful for kiosk and call-center deployments. Contact VoiceTel engineering for a template.</p>
